<b>References</b>
<br>
<br>
P. Griffiths and J. Harris, <em>Principles of algebraic geometry</em>, Wiley 2010. <a href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Sny48qKdW40C">googlebooks</a>.
<br>
<br>
M. Reid, <em>Undergraduate algebraic geometry</em>, C.U.P. 1988. <a href="https://books.google.com/books/about/Undergraduate_Algebraic_Geometry.html?id=KvKdSkPwwmMC">googlebooks</a>.
<br>
<br>
I. Dolgachev, <em>Classical algebraic geometry</em>. <a href="http://www.math.lsa.umich.edu/~idolga/lecturenotes.html">Lecture notes</a>.
<br>
<br>
J. Koll&aacute;r and S. Mori, <em>Birational geometry of algebraic varieties</em>, C.U.P 1998. <a href="https://books.google.com/books/about/Birational_Geometry_of_Algebraic_Varieti.html?id=YrysxvPbBLwC">googlebooks</a>.
<br>
<br>
S. Mori, <em>Projective manifolds with ample tangent bundles</em>, Ann. of Math. (2) 110 (1979), no. 3, 593--606. <a href="http://www.jstor.org/stable/1971241?origin=crossref&seq=1#page_scan_tab_contents">JSTOR</a>.
<br>
<br>
D. Cox, <em>What is a toric variety?</em>, in Topics in algebraic geometry and geometric modeling, 
Contemp. Math. 334, A.M.S., 2003, 203--223. <a href="tutorial.pdf">pdf</a>.
<br>
<br>
D. Cox, <em>Mirror symmetry and polar duality of polytopes</em>, Symmetry 7 (2015), 1633--1645. <a href="mirrorsymmetry.pdf">pdf</a>.
<br>
<br>
H. Clemens and P. Griffiths, <em>The intermediate Jacobian of the cubic threefold</em>, Ann. of Math. (2) 95 (1972), 281--356. <a href="http://www.jstor.org/stable/1970801?origin=crossref&seq=1#page_scan_tab_contents">JSTOR</a>.
<br>
<br>
B. Hassett, <em>Special cubic 4-folds</em>, Harvard PhD thesis, 1996. <a href="http://www.math.brown.edu/~bhassett/papers/cubics/cubiclong.pdf">pdf</a>.
